nly","Zona fasciculata only"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPrimary adrenocortical insufficiency (Addison disease) affects all three zones of the adrenal cortex:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EZona glomerulosa, zona fasciculata, and zona reticularis\u003C/strong\u003E are all affected, leading to deficiencies in mineralocorticoids, glucocorticoids, and androgens respectively\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezona glomerulosa and zona fasciculata\u003C/strong\u003E produce aldosterone and cortisol respectively\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezona fasciculata and zona reticularis\u003C/strong\u003E are regulated by adrenocorticotropic hormone\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezona glomerulosa and zona reticularis\u003C/strong\u003E are the outermost and innermost layers\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezona fasciculata\u003C/strong\u003E produces glucocorticoids and is the thickest layer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The adrenal cortex consists of three distinct zones: zona glomerulosa, zona fasciculata, and zona reticularis, which are all affected in primary adrenocortical insufficiency.","Each zone of the adrenal cortex produces different hormones: mineralocorticoids (glomerulosa), glucocorticoids (fasciculata), and androgens (reticularis)."],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine